THREE suspects are in hot water for allegedly kidnapping a 26-year-old man in Thabong, Free State, on Tuesday, 19 July. According to Captain Stephen Thakeng, the trio reportedly demanded a ransom of R30 000 to release the victim. He said a case of kidnapping was registered for further investigation. “On Sunday, 24 July, at about 3.30pm, information received from crime intelligence was followed by the Welkom Public Order Police Unit, Thabong Task Team and Thabong Serious and Violent Crimes Unit members, leading to the arrest of the suspects,” Thakeng said. ALSO READ: Tips to make cash on TikTok He said the trio is facing charges of kidnapping, assault, conspiracy to commit a crime, possession of unlicensed ammunition and contravention of the Immigration Act. The suspects, aged between 20 and 26, appeared in the Welkom Magistrates Court on Tuesday, 26 July. The case was postponed to 6 September for further investigation.